<br>
But better than anyone else, we all know that EQ is a problem in itself.  Spending hour after hour, day after day in front of the screen playing this game can become a problem.  <br>
<br>
No, it's not healthy, but who ever accused the human race of being smart anyways.  Millions smoke, knowing full well it's the cause of numerous diseases.  Like with everything else, there are always those who take it too far.  It's pretty simple really.  Just ask yourself: &quot;Can I lay off?&quot;.  If you can without the shadow of a doubt say YES, an not lie to yourself, no it's not a big deal.  If you have any doubts at all, you might be in more trouble than you think.<br>
<br>
Yes, some people have lost jobs/wife/husband/friends, etc over EQ.  It has become an obsession in many.  How many of you have ever cut work/school to play EQ???<br>
